      <item>
        <title>Taxonomy of Powered by the Apocalypse Games</title>
        <dc:creator><![CDATA[@nynphaiel]]></dc:creator>
        <description><![CDATA[
          <p><a href="https://forums.gauntlet-rpg.com/u/nynphaiel">@nynphaiel</a> wrote:</p>
          <blockquote>
              <p>Each layer has a different criteria, and each criteria has its own legend. Hope this helps <img src="https://forums.gauntlet-rpg.com/images/emoji/twitter/slight_smile.png?v=9" title=":slight_smile:" class="emoji" alt=":slight_smile:"></p>
<p><strong>XP:</strong><br>
Highlights<br>
By Playbook<br>
Misses<br>
Universal</p>
<p><strong>Structure:</strong><br>
Unstructured<br>
Phases<br>
Seasonal</p>
<p><strong>Playbooks:</strong><br>
Standard<br>
Modular<br>
Single-move</p>
<p><strong>Evenness:</strong><br>
Uneven PCs<br>
Even PCs</p>
<p><strong>Moves:</strong><br>
Basic + Playbook<br>
Universal</p>
<p><strong>Interpersonal Systems:</strong><br>
Hx<br>
Bonds<br>
Strings<br>
Debt</p>
<p><strong>Dice:</strong><br>
2d6 + [stat]<br>
best of [stat] cards<br>
Character tags<br>
2d10 + [stat]</p>
<p><strong>Death &amp; Harm:</strong><br>
Harm<br>
Optional death<br>
‘Sever harm’ move<br>
Structural</p>
<p><strong>Consequence tracks:</strong><br>
Stress</p>
<p><strong>Conditions:</strong><br>
Negative stats<br>
Freeform</p>
          </blockquote>
          <p><a href="https://forums.gauntlet-rpg.com/t/taxonomy-of-powered-by-the-apocalypse-games/6358/5">Read full topic</a></p>
        ]]></description>
